    {
        "content": "<p>tolumide-ng requested <a href=\"https://github.com/cfallin\">cfallin</a> for a review on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12805\">PR #12805</a>.</p>",
        "id": 580541764,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1773960663
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>tolumide-ng opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12805\">PR #12805</a> from <code>tolumide-ng:fix/wasmtime-c-api-gc-update</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The <code>c-api</code> crate currently enables the <code>gc</code> feature on its <code>wasmtime</code> dependency, even though it exposes a <code>gc</code> feature to control this behaviour. This prevents downstream users from disabling <code>gc</code>, since <code>Cargo.toml</code> doesn't allow overriding it. However, structs like <code>RootScope</code> are only available when <code>gc</code> is enabled. Removing it from default features, without other options, would break internal implementations.</p>\n<h3>Changes</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Enable the <code>gc</code> feature via the wasmtime-c-api crate by default.</li>\n<li>Removes the explicitly set <code>gc</code> feature for the <code>wasmtime</code> dependency in <code>c-api</code>, thus enabling downstream users to specify this behaviour.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Closes <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/12783\">https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/12783</a></p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 580541767,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1773960664
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>github-actions[bot] added the label <code>wasmtime:c-api</code> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12805\">PR #12805</a>.</p>",
        "id": 580565899,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1773973961
